# Customer Service Medewerker

>

CLdN CARGO is part of the CLdN Group, a solid and growing company. CLdN CARGO is one of Europe’s leading door-to-door logistics providers. We are an asset-based operator, split into three business units: Containers, Trailers and Forwarding. We offer total freight management solutions and complete services for all our customers' shipping and forwarding requirements. With an international team of almost 200 people, we focus on sustainable partnerships and provide tailor-made and innovative solutions in transport everywhere we g(r)o(w).

**_Are you looking for the next step in your career in a growing logistics company?_**

In order to ensure our ambitious expansion plan, CLdN CARGO is looking for motivated colleagues to support the team in our office in Zeebrugge. Within this dynamic function, you will be part of the Customer Service team who is responsible to process and follow up every trucking orders.

**Your role**

- Creation of the transport orders: make sure transit time and the delivery dates are met;

- Follow up of orders, costs, deadlines and keep clients updated on a constant basis;

- Ensure a smooth planification of the cargo;

- Propose solutions and react proactively;

- Handle for problems that may occur;

- …


**Your profile**

- You are fluent in English and Dutch;

- A first experience in customs is a plus;

- You have a first experience in the logistic / transport sector;

- You have a good knowledge of the Office packages;

- You are customer oriented and stress resistant;

- You are a real team player with a strong emphasis on accuracy, reliability and flexibility;

- You can think and act in a solution-oriented way.

- You are flexible and **ready to work in shifts between 07:30 and 18:00** (Monday to Friday).

- You meet the requirements to obtain a legally mandatory positive security clearance for critical functions in the port.


**Our offer**

- A stimulating working environment with positive and committed co-workers;

- A can-do attitude working environment and quick decision making;

- A workplace in our office in Zeebrugge with occasional option to work from home.


**Contact**

Are you interested in learning more about this position or do you want to apply? Do not hesitate to send your CV with a cover letter to [recruitment.be@cldn.com](mailto:recruitment.be@cldn.com) with reference “customer service officer”.

